  "claim_short": "Counterexample to Chapter 5 Problem 5 of arXiv:1902.05306 asking whether the dimension spectrum is generally encoded by D-only zeta functions zeta_{|D|^{-k},D}. In the diagonal regular spectral triple on l2(N) with D e_n = n e_n and U e_n = n^i e_n, the algebra element U is order zero and zeta_{U,D}(s)=zeta(s-i), giving a dimension-spectrum pole at 1+i, while all D-only probe poles are real points 1-k.",
